        "id": "c3bca3cdef8d7cb9",
        "text": "To set up column width and soft wrap (again, this must be done for each file) go to: 'Window' --> 'File Options...' --> 'Wrapping' in the left-hand column. Use the 'Soft Wrap Files' checkbox to have 'Pe' soft wrap the file every time it opens it. Set the 'Fixed Column:' number to 67 if you are working with gopher files, especially a gophermap. 'Pe' also has a nice button, 'Softwrap', the rightmost one that looks kind of like a newspaper or a document with two columns, to toggle soft wrap while editing a file. I recommend inserting the hard line breaks when you are done\nediting the file. Again, this will make the actual file contain lines that are of the length (column width) that you specify. 'Pe' can perform this operation on arbitrary selections of text. To do this on the whole file: Select all of the text, either by typing 'Alt-A' or by clicking 'Edit' --> 'Select All'. Then, click 'Text' --> 'Insert Linebreaks'. N.B. When editing a gophermap, you do not want to insert line breaks into the lines beginning with a number or letter code specifying an itemtype. Just keep your descriptions to 67 characters or less. Insert linebreaks into your paragraphs by individually selecting them and performing 'Insert Linebreaks.' N.B. It seems that soft wrap must be enabled in order to perform\nthe 'Insert Linebreaks' function."
